Several African countries have made their voices heard, about recent attacks on foreign nationals in South Africa. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - South Africa's national soccer team is having a difficult time finding a country to play due to ongoing xenophobic violence in the state. READ: Zambia friendly against Bafana Bafana called off The Madagascan national team withdrew their participation in an international friendly with Bafana Bafana, only two days after the Zambian team declined to play. Both international teams cited ongoing attacks against foreign nationals as the reason for their withdrawal. 